    "abstractNote": "The Syro-Oriental Metropolitan Bishop Elias of Nisibis (975-1046) was not only a remarkable theologian and also the most important Christian Arab author with regard to Christian-Muslim relations. He was, first of all, a pastor. Among the sapiential works written by our bishop in Arabic we know, for the moment, of just one manuscript of the song intitled <i>Tasbihat Mar Iliyya Mutran Nasibin</i>, which we were able to consult at the Biblioth\u00e8que Nationale of Paris. This manuscript is published here for the first time along with a French translation. The Song of Elias of Nisibis, which is part of a prayer book from the Melkite Church, gives us a first insight into the spirituality of Elias, who is especially known for his love of demonstrative syllogism and clarity of language.",
